{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603119","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603119"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:32:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:32:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15712"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15712","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15712"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8403"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113932"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8403","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8403"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15712"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"95947"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"7037"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20244"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20247"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"113932","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/113932"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ovary contains several distinct tissue types that serve different reproductive and endocrine functions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following comprises the bulk of ovarian tissue?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hilus cells","Surface epithelium","Stroma","Follicles","Blood vessels"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Estroma\u003C/strong\u003E forms the majority of ovarian tissue and consists of specialized connective tissue containing steroid-producing cells. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ehilus cells\u003C/strong\u003E are located in the central portion where blood vessels enter the ovary, whilst the \u003Cstrong\u003Esurface epithelium\u003C/strong\u003E is a single layer of cells covering the ovary. \u003Cstrong\u003EFollicles\u003C/strong\u003E are embedded within the stroma but occupy a relatively small proportion of the total ovarian volume, and \u003Cstrong\u003Eblood vessels\u003C/strong\u003E enter through the hilum and branch throughout the organ but do not constitute the bulk of the tissue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe stroma is crucial for:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EProviding structural support\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHousing steroid-producing cells\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESupporting follicular development\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EContributing to hormone production\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The ovarian stroma forms the bulk of ovarian tissue and consists of connective tissue containing steroid-producing cells.","Ovarian follicles are embedded within the stroma but do not constitute the majority of ovarian volume."],"references":["O\u0027Neill KE, Maher JY, Laronda MM, Duncan FE, LeDuc RD, Lujan ME, Oktay KH, Pouch AM, Segars JH, Tsui EL, Zelinski MB, Halvorson LM, Gomez-Lobo V. Anatomic nomenclature and 3-dimensional regional model of the human ovary: call for a new paradigm. Am J Obstet Gynecol. 2023 Mar;228(3):270-275.e4. doi: 10.1016/j.ajog.2022.09.040. Epub 2022 Sep 30. PMID: 36191605; PMCID: PMC9974561.","Richards JS, Pangas SA. The ovary: basic biology and clinical implications. J Clin Invest. 2010 Apr;120(4):963-72. doi: 10.1172/JCI41350. Epub 2010 Apr 1. PMID: 20364094; PMCID: PMC2846061.","Schlafer DH, Foster RA. Female Genital System. Jubb, Kennedy \u0026 Palmer\u0027s Pathology of Domestic Animals: Volume 3. 2016:358\u2013464.e1. do